cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new data structure for storing and searching genomic databases efficiently. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper discusses a method for searching for occurrences of a pattern in a string, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the time and space complexity of the proposed method. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper uses concepts from discrete mathematics, such as straight-line programs and LZ77 parse, in the construction of the self-index. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper may involve some geometric concepts in the construction of the self-index, as genomic data can be represented as sequences of nucleotides that can be visualized as points in a high-dimensional space.
